      "running_accuracy": 0.6667,
      "explanation": "The correct answer is B. \"Accuracy\" refers to the closeness to the true value, as it is the measure of how close the measured value is to the actual value. This is not explicitly mentioned in the given excerpts, but it is a fundamental concept in measurement systems. \"Precision\", on the other hand, refers to the repeatability of readings, or the consistency of the measurement system. This is supported by Excerpt 2, which discusses the nature of measurement required, including the accuracy and reliability required. The student's answer, B, correctly identifies the difference between accuracy and precision."
